<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-04-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-04-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1144" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1144">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Andrade</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States of Venezuela</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-04-23"><hi rend="italic">April
                                        23, 1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of the communication of the 22d instant, in which your
                            excellency inserts the rules which the Government of the United States
                            proposes to observe in the case, now imminent, of hostilities with
                            Spain, and to inform you that I have, by to-day’s mail, communicated its
                            contents to my Government.</p>
                        <p>I avail myself, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">José Andrade.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>